<h2>Frequently Asked Questions — LG Washer Repair Cost</h2>

<h3>How much does LG washer repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>Most LG washer repairs run $150–480 depending on the part — common fixes like a drain pump or door seal land around $280–360, while a bearing or motor runs higher. A simple clog or balancing issue is often just the service call.</p>

<h3>Is the diagnostic fee separate from the repair cost?</h3>
<p>The $65 diagnostic is a separate fee only if you don't proceed — it's waived entirely when you approve the repair. So for almost every job you pay the repair price, not the repair price plus a diagnostic. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Why do some LG washer repairs cost so much more than others?</h3>
<p>The difference is labor depth and the part. A clogged filter is a few minutes; a drum bearing means pulling the drum and splitting the tub, which is a 2–3 hour job. The part price varies too — a pump is modest, a control board or motor is not.</p>

<h3>Is it cheaper to repair or replace my LG washer?</h3>
<p>For most single-part failures, repair is cheaper — $150–480 versus $800–1,500 for a comparable new LG washer. Replacing makes sense mainly when an older machine has several major parts failing at once, and we'll tell you honestly which situation you're in.</p>

<h3>Do you charge extra for same-day or weekend LG washer repair?</h3>
<p>No — our pricing is the same for same-day and weekend service, with no surcharge. You pay the repair price plus parts; the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the work.</p>

